@*
    Lists the mustache placeholders admins can reference inside an
    organisation-wide editable file (always-included files, the
    .code-workspace template). Reads from MustacheVariableCatalog so the hint
    and the generator's actual substitution table can never drift apart.

    Per-file / volatile vars ({{name}}, {{moduleName}}, {{namespace}},
    {{guid}}) are intentionally not surfaced here - see the
    AvailableInAdminContent flag on each catalogue entry.
*@
@using ALDevToolbox.Domain.ValueObjects

<details class="mustache-hint">
    <summary>
        <Icon Name="lightbulb" Width="14" Height="14" />
        <span>Available template variables</span>
    </summary>
    <p class="muted mustache-hint__intro">
        These resolve at generation time when <strong>variable substitution</strong>
        is enabled for the file. Wrap the name in double braces, e.g.
        <code>{{publisher}}</code>.
    </p>
    <dl class="mustache-hint__list">
        @foreach (var v in MustacheVariableCatalog.ForAdminContent)
        {
            <dt><code>@($"{{{{{v.Name}}}}}")</code></dt>
            <dd>@v.Caption</dd>
        }
    </dl>
</details>
